DefaultAnalyzer - Class in version_five
Analyzes stats from a bunch of questions, predicting when the question needs to be asked again based on past performance and the equation: r = e^(-t / s) where r is the percentage the question will be answered correctly, t is time, and s is the weight.
DefaultAnalyzer(double) - Constructor for class version_five.DefaultAnalyzer
Constructs an empty analyzer, will not be accurate until more questions are added.
DefaultAnalyzer(double, List<IQuestion>) - Constructor for class version_five.DefaultAnalyzer
Constructs an analyzer with base values taken from the array of questions (note the list of questions will not be edited by this class).
DefaultEngine - Class in version_five

DefaultEngine() - Constructor for class version_five.DefaultEngine
Construct the default engine that uses command line to display and input data.
DefaultFileManager - Class in version_five
